I""<p>Here’s my attempt at explaining my research in three minutes. It’s anchored to the story of Jean-Dominuque Bauby, a French fashion editor who was left almost completely paralysed after a severe stroke in 1995. He described his experience of living with <em>locked-in syndrome</em> in his 1997 memoir <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/193755.The_Diving_Bell_and_the_Butterfly">The Divingbell and the Butterfly</a>.</p>

<p>I haven’t watched this. For all I know the sound cuts out after 5 seconds. All I can say is it was at least good enough to get a place in the final.</p>

